\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2525755\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 21, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104all1665702923490.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/all1665702923490.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/all1665702923490.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"all1665702923490\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Development Considerations for Performance and Scalability\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"all1665702923490__development_considerations_for_performance_and_scalability_140650\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">During development, the focus of performance optimization measures is primarily on component design and ProcScript coding.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"all1665702923490__p_d46037e1_d46038e1_d46039e1\">For example, aim to do the following:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"all1665702923490__li_d22991e1_d22992e1_d22993e1\">Implement asynchronous or stateless requests whenever possible\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"all1665702923490__li_d22994e1_d22995e1_d22996e1\">Retrieve appropriate amounts of data. For example, use stepped hitlists, or create a service to return only the entity field required rather than all fields\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"all1665702923490__li_d22997e1_d22998e1_d22999e1\">Reuse retrieved data rather than requesting it each time.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"all1665702923490__li_d23000e1_d23001e1_d23002e1\">Use correct data types to reduce conversions\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"all1665702923490__li_d23003e1_d23004e1_d23005e1\">Implement data processing at the appropriate level (entity or occurrence)\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"all1665702923490__li_d23006e1_d23007e1_d23008e1\">Use include ProcScript operations in preference to global ProcScript operations. This can improve encapsulation, which in turn assists with flexibility in deployment\n </li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ezv1705470008998.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Component Memory Management</a><p>At runtime, component instances require memory to handle the component definition and component data. This memory is not necessarily freed when the component instance is deleted.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2525755\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2525755\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Development Considerations for Performance and Scalability Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 21, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Development Considerations for Performance and Scalability During development, the focus of performance optimization measures is primarily on component design and ProcScript coding. For example, aim to do the following: Implement asynchronous or stateless requests whenever possible Retrieve appropriate amounts of data. For example, use stepped hitlists, or create a service to return only the entity field required rather than all fields Reuse retrieved data rather than requesting it each time. Use correct data types to reduce conversions Implement data processing at the appropriate level (entity or occurrence) Use include ProcScript operations in preference to global ProcScript operations. This can improve encapsulation, which in turn assists with flexibility in deployment Related Links Component Memory Management At runtime, component instances require memory to handle the component definition and component data. This memory is not necessarily freed when the component instance is deleted. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}